      <title>Taiwan and Japan scramble jets after Chinese incursion</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANTaiwan and Japan both scrambled jets over the weekend after Chinese aircraft  incursions. According to Taiwan's Ministry of National Defense, or MND, two Chinese military aircraft crossed the median line of the Taiwan Strait at 11 a.m.  According to the MND, the Taiwan Air Force scrambled jets to intercept the two J-11 fighter planes. According to a statement issued by the MND, the Chinese planes retreated to the west side of the median line after they were issued a radio warning.  According to CNN, on Saturday, the Japanese Self-Defense Force announced it also scrambled fighters after Chinese aircraft flew between the Japanese islands of Okinawa and Miyako. Japan's Self Defense Forces said in a statement that the Chinese air force had sent four Xian H-6K long range bombers, one Shaanxi Y-8 electronic countermeasures aircraft, one Tupolev Tu-154 MD electronic intelligence plane and at least two fighter jets through international airspace between the two islands on Saturday. According to the AFP, the flights come a week after the U.S. sailed a destroyer and a coast guard ship through the Taiwan Strait, angering Beijing. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Chinese aircraft crossing median line, Taiwanese aircraft scrambled to intercept2. Chinese aircraft returning to the west of median line after being warned3. Japan scrambling jets to intercept Chinese aircraft4. Chinese aircraft that flew between Okinawa and Miyako islandsVOICEOVER (in English): "According to Taiwan's Ministry of National Defense, or MND, two Chinese military aircraft crossed the median line of the Taiwan Strait at 11 a.m. on Sunday."  "According to the MND, the Taiwan Air Force scrambled jets to intercept the two J-11 fighter planes." "According to a statement issued by the MND, the Chinese planes retreated to the west side of the median line after they were issued a radio warning."  "According to CNN, on Saturday, the Japanese Self-Defense Force announced it also scrambled fighters after Chinese aircraft flew between the Japanese islands of Okinawa and Miyako." "Japan's Self Defense Forces said in a statement that the Chinese air force had sent four Xian H-6K long range bombers, one Shaanxi Y-8 electronic countermeasures aircraft, one Tupolev Tu-154 MD electronic intelligence plane and at least two fighter jets through international airspace between the two islands on Saturday." SOURCES: Focus Taiwan, CNN, AFP http://focustaiwan.tw/news/aipl/201903310007.aspxhttps://edition.cnn.com/2019/04/01/asia/china-japan-taiwan-jets-intl/index.htmlhttps://news.yahoo.com/taiwan-blasts-china-reckless-fighter-jet-incursion-150050734.html***]]></description>
