rticle to its target site.""The robots used in the study were 35 hundreths of a millimeter long." "They were printed via a 3D printer and then coated with nickel, making them magnetic. This allows them to be controlled via an external magnetic field.""The researchers applied a magnetic field onto the tiny robot which allowed it to rotate as it traveled through the bloodstream, creating a convection current.""The researchers mainly used the nanoparticles to target disease sites around blood vessels that are 'leaky' such as tumors." SOURCES: MIT News, Phys.org, Science Magazine    http://news.mit.edu/2019/nanoparticles-magnetic-robots-0426https://phys.org/news/2019-04-tiny-robots-powered-magnetic-fields.htmlhttps://advances.sciencemag.org/content/5/4/eaav4803.full***]]></description>
